Summary
Root cause: In RelationSetup.vue's makeComboRender() (used for the LEFT_CLS_IDS / REG_TYPE_ID cell renderers), when the linkParam array is empty — exactly the case for a brand-new row created via "Create," which starts with LEFT_CLS_IDS: null — the code did:


linkParam.forEach(v => { ... })          // no iterations, nothing appended
if (link.lastChild.nodeType == ...)      // link.lastChild is null → throws
That TypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading 'nodeType') matches exactly the console error you shared. It's thrown inside AG Grid's cellRenderer, called synchronously from grid.ensureIndexVisible(...) — the last line of insertRows(), right after onShowLoading() had already set the grid's loading flag to true. Since the exception aborted the function before onHideLoading() could run, the grid loading overlay was left stuck forever. It only reproduces on grids with lots of existing data because that's when the new row needs fresh cell rendering (via scroll-into-view) instead of reusing an already-rendered cell.

Fix applied in RelationSetup.vue:

Line 1163: guarded link.lastChild?.nodeType against null.
Wrapped insertRows's body in try/finally so onHideLoading() always runs even if a future rendering error occurs — prevents this class of bug from causing a stuck spinner again.
No further AG Grid destroyed-instance or Brotli console messages you saw are related to this (those are unrelated background noise). Please retest Create on the same data-heavy grid to confirm.
